cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the challenges and ethical issues related to sampling professional software developers for survey research. The focus is on empirical software engineering research, which falls under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. The paper also touches upon issues related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC), cybersecurity (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper highlights the need to maintain a collection of key demographics about software developers, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
